    • Method Detail

      • awake

        public abstract void awake()
        This function is always called right after adding a behaviour to a game object in the same frame even when the game object is disabled.

      • start

        public abstract void start()
        This function is called before the first frame update when the script is enabled.

      • fixedUpdate

        public abstract void fixedUpdate()
        This method runs at a fixed delta time unrelated to framerate, therefore it can be executed multiple times a frame if needed. All physics calculations and other behaviour update methods occur immediately after fixedUpdate.

      • update

        public abstract void update(float delta)
        Update is called once a frame.
        Parameters:
        delta - The delta time from last to current frame. Graphics.getDeltaTime()

      • lateUpdate

        public abstract void lateUpdate(float delta)
        This method is called once per frame after update(float) is finished. For example, you can use this to adjust the cameras position after a players position changed.
        Parameters:
        delta - The delta time from last to current frame. Graphics.getDeltaTime()

      • onCollisionPreSolve

        Parameters:

        contact - Infos about the collision.
        oldManifold - Manifold

                                      com.badlogic.gdx.physics.box2d.Contact contact)
        This method gets called when a Box2D collision happens with this object.
        Parameters:
        other - The other object this object collides with or null when it collides with a non unbox2d body.
        contact - Infos about the collision.

      • onCollisionStay

        public abstract void onCollisionStay(Behaviour other)
        This method gets continuously called once per fixed update when a collision still occurs. However, this method isn't executed when the body is colliding with a non unbox2d body.
        Parameters:
        other - The other object this object collides with.

      • onCollisionExit

        public abstract void onCollisionExit(Behaviour other,
                                     com.badlogic.gdx.physics.box2d.Contact contact)
        This method gets called when a Box2D collision stops with this object or null when it collides with a non unbox2d body.
        Parameters:
        other - The other object this object stopped colliding with.
        contact - Infos about the collision.

      • render

        public abstract void render(com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.Batch batch)
        A method which draws the behaviour onto the screen once a frame.
        Parameters:
        batch - The batch which is used to draw the behaviour.

      • debugRender

        public abstract void debugRender(com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.glutils.ShapeRenderer render)
        A method which uses a ShapeRenderer to draw the behaviour to the screen once a frame. Therefore, most commonly used to draw debug infos.
        Parameters:
        render - The shape renderer which is used to draw the behaviour.

      • debugRender

        public abstract void debugRender(space.earlygrey.shapedrawer.ShapeDrawer drawer)
        A method which uses a ShapeDrawer to draw the behaviour to the screen once a frame. Therefore, most commonly used to draw debug infos.
        Parameters:
        drawer - The shape renderer which is used to draw the behaviour.

      • onEnable

        public abstract void onEnable()
        When a game object gets enabled with GameObject.setEnabled(boolean) this method gets immediately called.

      • onDisable

        public abstract void onDisable()
        This method gets called in three ways:
        • When a game object gets disabled with GameObject.setEnabled(boolean) this method gets immediately called.
        • When a game object gets destroyed and the game object is enabled.
        • When a game object is enabled and this behaviour got removed from that game object.

      • onDestroy

        public abstract void onDestroy()
        This function is called when the behaviour gets cleaned up in UnBox.postRender(). For example if you UnBox.destroy(GameObject) the game object or the behaviour itself.

      • destroy

        public void destroy()
        Marks the behaviour for deletion at the end of the current frame.
